When the result of a PAD tag is false the part after {tag 'else'} is used.

{page 'constructs/else_1'}

<hr>The else concept is a general feature of a PAD tag, applies to all PAD tags.<br><br>

{example 'constructs/else_4'}

<hr>When the result of a PAD tag is an empty array the part after {at 'else'} is used.

{page 'constructs/else_2'}

<hr>The else context can also be given with the 'else' option at the tag itself.

